# VCD to DataFrame Conversion Libraries

## Main Goal

### Technical Description

Create libraries that convert VCD (Value Change Dump) files into data frames that can be analyzed using languages such as Python or R.

### Human-Readable Description

Create tools that turn raw hardware simulation data into spreadsheet-like tables that are easier to analyze using data science tools.

The goal is to:

* Make hardware simulation data easier to work with
* Allow researchers to use common data science tools on hardware traces
* Support both small and large hardware designs without excessive computation

---

# Purpose

## Technical Description

Develop frameworks that scale to hardware designs of any size without causing excessive computational overhead.

## Human-Readable Description

The system is designed so that even very large hardware simulations can be processed efficiently.

Instead of overwhelming the computer with huge trace files, the framework organizes and simplifies the data so it can be analyzed using tools like:

* R
* Python pandas
* Apache Spark

